    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-30T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-30T02:35:00-05:00" n="460"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1789: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-30T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >September 30, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 1—8:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>173. The British Minister informs me that Eden has informed Maisky<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d460fn52">Ivan Maisky, Soviet Ambassador in the United
                        Kingdom.</note> that he considers any undue interference in Iranian affairs
                    or sympathy towards separatist movements by Russian forces in north of Iran
                    would be most harmful. The Ambassador promised to communicate this information
                    to his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
